column1: The data on this page, drawn from BEA's various economic accounts, comprise an overview of the U.S. economy in recent quarters. Please explore other pages on our site for additional detail. Series marked with an "*" are based on "real" estimates that are calculated using a chain-type Fisher formula; annual chain-type measures are calculated with annual weights and quarterly chain-type measures are calculated with quarterly weights.  Series marked with a "#" are based on current-dollar estimates.
Percent change at seasonally adjusted annual rate (unless otherwise noted)
Government consumption expenditures and gross investment*
Real disposable personal income in the U.S.*
Billions of dollars, seasonally adjusted annual rate (unless otherwise noted)
Net state and local government saving
Note: Data on this page incorporate estimates from:
the GDP news release of March 25, 2016.
the State Personal Income news release of March 24, 2016.
the U.S. International Transactions news release of March 17, 2016.
